- Concept: What is a display list, why we need it (cache parsing results; multi-threading data structure - one thread parses, another renders). It's an fz_display_list struct holding a serialized stream of drawing commands.
- The value: "record once, play back many times" - decouples the expensive "interpret page" step from the cheap "replay" step.
- Key source: struct fz_display_list (list-device.c:147-154), fz_new_display_list (list-device.c:1667-1677), fz_keep/drop_display_list, fz_bound_display_list, fz_display_list_is_empty.
